 key:value  :  ,  {}  ,

```python
d = {key1 : value1, key2 : value2 }
```

dict  Python  dict




```python
tinydict = {'Alice': '2341', 'Beth': '9102', 'Cecil': '3258'}
tinydict1 = { 'abc': 456 }
tinydict2 = { 'abc': 123, 98.6: 37 }
```

## 

```python
thisdict =	{
  "brand": "Porsche",
  "model": "911",
  "year": 1963
}
x = thisdict["model"]
print(x)
```

## 

```
thisdict =	{
  "brand": "Porsche",
  "model": "911",
  "year": 1963
}
thisdict["year"] = 2019
```

## 

 for 






```
for x in thisdict:
  print(x)
```


 items() 

```
for x, y in thisdict.items():
  print(x, y)
```

## 



```
thisdict =	{
  "brand": "Porsche",
  "model": "911",
  "year": 1963
}
thisdict.pop("model")
print(thisdict)
```

## 

pop() 

```
thisdict =	{
  "brand": "Porsche",
  "model": "911",
  "year": 1963
}
thisdict.pop("model")
print(thisdict)
```

del ()

``` 
thisdict =	{
  "brand": "Porsche",
  "model": "911",
  "year": 1963
}
del thisdict["model"]
print(thisdict)
```

## dict()

 dict() 

``` 
thisdict = dict(brand="Porsche", model="911", year=1963)
# 
# 
print(thisdict)
```
